Checklist before considering the frontend done


 No <script> tag, no .js file, anywhere in the generated web-frontend module

 Registering as each of the 3 self-service roles, then logging in, lands on the correct role-specific dashboard

 A CUSTOMER session cannot reach /restaurant-owner/**, /delivery/**, or /admin/** (verify by typing the URL directly — Spring Security should redirect/403, not silently render)

 Submitting an invalid form (e.g. empty required field) re-renders the same page with field-level error text and the user's other input preserved — no blank form, no stack trace

 Adding an item from a second restaurant to the cart shows the backend's MultiRestaurantCartException message as a readable flash error, not a raw exception page

 The full happy path works end-to-end through the UI only, no API tools: register → browse → add to cart → checkout → (as owner) accept/prepare/ready → dispatch → (as partner) pick up/deliver → (as customer) pay → review

 Admin can approve a pending restaurant and it then appears in the public /restaurants listing


This closes out the full-stack build. At this point you have a working, demonstrable system through a real browser UI — a good place to write the project README and record a short walkthrough if this is going in a portfolio.

